  "id": "b2210fe4f9344a7b",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/snowflake/d524f547-c952-40a6-b17e-c104113f501e/application",
    "company": "Snowflake",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "b2210fe4f9344a7b",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nThe Snowflake Customer Experience Center (CEC) is seeking an experienced and highly motivated Briefing Program Manager to join our team. The successful candidate will be responsible for managing in-person executive meetings between our executive team and customers/partners in our Customer Experience Center in Menlo Park, as well as during our yearly Summit conference in San Francisco and occasional conferences. Additionally, the CEC Manager will play a key role in improving our CEC process, including building assets, creating best practices guides, developing agenda templates, and harnessing AI to improve the process as a whole.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n - Plan and manage all aspects of executive meetings in our CEC space in Menlo Park, including scheduling, logistics, and coordination with internal and external stakeholders.\n\n - Develop and implement best practices for CEC meetings, including agenda templates, email templates, and other assets that support a seamless and productive experience for our customers.\n\n - Work closely with the sales team to understand their needs and goals for each meeting, and ensure that the agenda and other materials reflect those goals.\n\n - Build and maintain relationships with key stakeholders, including customers, partners, and internal teams.\n\n - Continually evaluate and improve our CEC process based on customer feedback and industry best practices.\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS:\n\n - Bachelor's degree in business, marketing, or a related field.\n\n - 5+ years of experience in managing executive meetings or events, preferably in a technology or B2B environment.\n\n - Strong project management skills and ability to manage multiple priorities simultaneously.\n\n - Excellent written and verbal communication skills, including the ability to communicate with executive-level stakeholders.\n\n - Strong analytical skills and ability to use data to make informed decisions.\n\n - Familiarity with EBC best practices and trends, and experience implementing them in a real-world setting.\n\n - Proficiency in Microsoft Office, Google Suite and event management software - familiarity with BriefingSource is a plus.\n\n\nREQUIREMENTS:\n\n - Expected to have several years of experience in managing executive meetings or events. This experience may include planning, executing, and managing events or meetings for senior-level executives and customers.\n\n - Excellent written and verbal communication skills are essential for CEC Managers. They must be able to effectively communicate with internal and external stakeholders, including senior-level executives, customers, and partners.\n\n - CEC Managers must be able to think strategically and develop a clear vision for the CEC program. They should be able to identify and prioritize the needs of key stakeholders and develop effective strategies to meet those needs.\n\n - Project Management Skills: Strong project management skills are essential for CEC Managers. They must be able to manage multiple projects simultaneously, set priorities, and ensure that deadlines are met. High attention to detail is essential.\n\n - Customer Focus: CEC Managers must have a customer-focused mindset and be able to develop strong relationships with customers and partners. They should be able to understand customer needs and expectations and ensure that those needs are met during CEC meetings.\n\n - Overall, the CEC Manager should be a highly motivated and proactive individual who can work independently and collaboratively to achieve the goals of the CEC program. They should have a strong customer focus and be able to create a positive and productive environment for all stakeholders involved.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
